The paper discusses security issues in neural networks and proposes a novel framework for inserting malicious hardware Trojans in the implementation of a neural network classifier. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses potential defenses to protect neural networks against hardware Trojan attacks, which suggests that it may also belong to the cs.SE (Software Engineering) and cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) sub-categories.
